data.title: Team USA
data.meta_description: Explore the official website of Team USA. Get the latest news, athlete profiles, and updates on the US Olympic Team.
data.text:
Olivia Reeves Wins Weightlifting Gold for Team USA

Reeves set a new Olympic record in the snatch portion of the event after completing a 117 kg. (257 lb.) lift. She also is the first U.S. athlete to win an Olympic weightlifting gold medal since 2000.

ResultsNext slide: 'King Ben' Rai Benjamin is Golden in the 400-Meter Hurdles

'King Ben' Rai Benjamin is Golden in the 400-Meter Hurdles

Benjamin got the best of his rivals, Norway's Karsten Warholm and Brazil's Alison dos Santos, for Olympic gold. The trio will surely run it back throughout the track & field season leading up to the Olympic Games Los Angeles 2028.

ResultsNext slide: Helen Maroulis Wins Bronze, Becomes First U.S. Wrestler to Win Three Olympic Medals

18-Year-Old Kristina Teachout Wins Bronze in Taekwondo

The teenager from Florida battles back from the repechage to take home a medal in her first Olympic Games.

ResultsNext slide: Spencer Lee Takes Silver

Spencer Lee Takes Silver

Lee and his opponent were tied heading into the final seconds. But since his opponent's points came on a higher-scoring move, he was awarded the tie-breaking decision

ResultsNext slide: Aaron Brooks Battles Back for Bronze

Jefferson, Terry, Thomas and Richardson Take Women's 4x100-Meter Gold

Richardson ran the fastest anchor leg of the field (10.09 seconds) to run away with the top spot on the podium

ResultsNext slide: Men's Volleyball Bounces Back for Bronze

Men's Volleyball Bounces Back for Bronze

After not emerging from the group stage in Tokyo and enduring a heartbreaking loss to Poland in the semifinals in Paris, the veteran men's volleyball team defeated a world-class Italy team to secure bronze

ResultsNext slide: Jennifer Valente and Lily Williams Take 4th in Women's Madison, the best-ever U.S. Finish

Jennifer Valente and Lily Williams Take 4th in Women's Madison, the best-ever U.S. Finish

The marathon-like lap race that involves scoring points on certain laps and tagging in your teammate on-the-fly has been on the Olympic program five times, just twice for the women.

ResultsNext slide: Duffy Takes Fourth In Boutlder & Lead Final

Duffy Takes Fourth In Boutlder & Lead Final

Duffy came up just shorter than he would have liked to on the lead wall. But, he still place three spots higher than he did at Tokyo 2020.

ResultsNext slide: Teachout Heads to Repechage, Nickloas Will Fight for Bronze

Teachout Heads to Repechage, Nickloas Will Fight for Bronze

Teachout was ousted in the quarterfinals. NIckolas lost a tight semifinal bout in the final 2 seconds of the round. Both have a shot at redemption and a podium spot

Next slide: Men's Water Polo Drops Semifinal Match Against Serbia, Will Play for Bronze

Men's Water Polo Drops Semifinal Match Against Serbia, Will Play for Bronze

The match was tight from the first whistle to the last. But the offense could not find a way past Serbia's world-class goaltender. The U.S. lost 10-6.

ResultsNext slide: Loschiavo Earns Spot in 10m Platform Semifinal

Loschiavo Earns Spot in 10m Platform Semifinal

The semifinals are scheduled to begin at 10 a.m. Paris time on Saturday, August 10, with the finals slated for 3 p.m.

ResultsNext slide: Steph Curry Drops 36 as Team USA Defeats Nikola Jokic and Serbia For a Spot in the Finals

Steph Curry Drops 36 as Team USA Defeats Nikola Jokic and Serbia For a Spot in the Finals

The U.S. men's basketball team roared back from a double-digit deficit in the fourth quarter as Steph Curry records the highest-ever points by an American in a semifinal game.

ResultsNext slide: Grant Holloway Completes Redemption Tour, Takes Gold in 110-Meter Hurdles, Roberts Silver

Grant Holloway Completes Redemption Tour, Takes Gold in 110-Meter Hurdles, Roberts Silver

The silver medalist from the Olympic Games Tokyo 2020 is now golden. Roberts, who won bronze at the 2023 world championships, lunged to silver despite clipping several hurdles.

ResultsNext slide: Sydney McLaughlin-Levrone Takes Gold in World-Record Time, Anna Cockrell Wins Silver

Sydney McLaughlin-Levrone Takes Gold in World-Record Time, Anna Cockrell Wins Silver

The queen of the 400-meter hurdles made no mistake, leaving the field behind to finish in 50.37 seconds. Cockrell finished over a second later for silver, while Jasmine Jones narrowly missed the sweep, coming in 4th behind Femke Bol.

ResultsNext slide: Tara Davis-Woodhall Takes Gold, Jasmine Moore Bronze in Long Jump

Tara Davis-Woodhall Takes Gold, Jasmine Moore Bronze in Long Jump

Davis-Woodhall soared in the air to score a 7.10-meter jump, while Moore's 6.96-meter leap secured a podium finish for her second medal in Paris.

ResultsNext slide: 'Kung-Fu' Kenny Bednarek Takes Silver, Lyles Gets Bronze in Men's 200 Meters

Women's Volleyball Defeats Brazil, Heads to Gold-Medal Match

The longtime rivals squared off in the semifinals three years after the U.S. defeated Brazil for gold in Tokyo. The U.S. prevailed once more to earn the right to defend its title.

ResultsNext slide: Nevin Harrison Sprints Her Way to the Finals

Watson Breaks World Record to Take Speed Climbing Bronze

The time was faster than that of Reza Alipour Shenazandifard of Iran, who had a result of 4.88 seconds, giving Watson the bronze.

ResultsNext slide: Indiana's Carson Tyler Places Fourth in Men's 3-Meter Springboard

Brooke Raboutou advances to the final round of women's boulder and lead sport climbing

The final round will be held Saturday, August 10, with the boulder competition scheduled to begin at 10:15 a.m. Paris time, followed by the lead at 12:35 p.m.

ResultsNext slide: Sarah Hildebrandt Wins the Second U.S. Women's Wrestling Gold in as Many Days

Sarah Hildebrandt Wins the Second U.S. Women's Wrestling Gold in as Many Days

The Indiana native did not let a switch-up in opponents faze her, as she defeated her opponent 3-0 in the gold-medal match

ResultsNext slide: The U.S. Artistic Swimming Team Wins Silver, the Best Finish Since 1996

The U.S. Artistic Swimming Team Wins Silver, the Best Finish Since 1996

The US squad posted a score of 282.7567, less than 5 points out of silver medal position. Competition continues with the team free routine, scheduled for 7:30 p.m. Paris time on August 6

ResultsNext slide: Kenneth Rooks Stuns Steeplechase Favorites for Silver

Kenneth Rooks Stuns Steeplechase Favorites for Silver

The long-distance men of Team USA continue to impress the world as Rooks ran step-for-step with the leaders to the finish line.

ResultsNext slide: Quincy Hall Surges to Gold in the Finals Steps of the Men's 400 Meters

Quincy Hall Surges to Gold in the Finals Steps of the Men's 400 Meters

Hall found an extra gear in the final 60 meters to pass the field for the win and a personal best.

ResultsNext slide: Katie Moon Soars to Silver in Women's Pole Vault

Katie Moon Soars to Silver in Women's Pole Vault

Moon, who took gold in Tokyo, battled her rival, Nina Kennedy of Australia to the wire. But Kennedy got the best of her tonight.

ResultsNext slide: Kristen Faulkner, Chloe Dygert, Lily Williams and Jennifer Valente Take Team Pursuit Gold

Hampton Morris Wins First U.S. Men's Weightlifting Medal Since 1984

Morris, who is just 20 years old, went for silver on his last lift but could not complete the jerk, and won bronze. Morris currently holds the junior and senior world records in the men's 61 kg. clean & jerk.

ResultsNext slide: Tom Schaar Wins Silver In Men's Park

Ecker, Small into Men's Single Kayak 1000m Quarterfinals

Both return to the water for quarterfinal races that begin at 2:10 p.m. Paris time on Wednesday. A top two finish in their quarterfinal would advance them to the semifinal round, scheduled for 11:10 a.m. on Saturday, August 10.

ResultsNext slide: Amit Elor Becomes Youngest U.S. Wrestler to Win Gold

Hocker Stuns Stacked Men's 1500 Field For Gold, Nuguse Gets Bronze as U.S. Makes History

This is the first time the U.S. has had two men earn Olympic medals in the men's 1500-meter final since 1912.

ResultsNext slide: Sophia Smith's Goal in Extra Time Sends the USWNT to Its First Gold-Medal Match Since 2012

Sophia Smith's Goal in Extra Time Sends the USWNT to Its First Gold-Medal Match Since 2012

Mallory Swanson's threaded a sensational through-ball to Smith near the top of the box, and Smith used her left foot to send it past the German keeper and into the left side of the net. The USWNT hung on to win 1-0.

ResultsNext slide: Wettstein Finishes Sixth in Women's Park Skateboard, Tying Personal Best

Wettstein Finishes Sixth in Women's Park Skateboard, Tying Personal Best

Wettstein had the second-best score in the preliminaries, an 85.65, to move into the final round. After nailing a solid first run in finals, Wettstein reaches for more points in run 3. Unfortunately, she could not complete her final trick.

ResultsNext slide: Hildebrandt Gains Semifinal Round in Wrestling Women's 50kg

Hildebrandt Gains Semifinal Round in Wrestling Women's 50kg

Reigning Olympic bronze medalist Sarah Hildebrandt advanced to the semifinal round of the women's 50kg division during wrestling action Tuesday at the Champs de Mars Arena.

ResultsNext slide: Raboutou, Grossman in Top Five After Boulder Semifinal

Ecker and Small Advance to Men's Double Kayak 500m Semifinal

The duo reached the finish line in 1:28.93, good for third in their quarterfinal as well as the third-fastest of the field.

ResultsNext slide: Caroline Marks Wins Women's Surfing Gold by 0.18 Points

Caroline Marks Wins Women's Surfing Gold by 0.18 Points

Battling calm conditions that produced limited waves, Marks' chess move of holding priority paid off. She scored the lone wave with a barrel to hang on for the win.

ResultsNext slide: Valarie Allman Becomes First U.S. Woman to Win Back-to-Back Discus Golds

Valarie Allman Becomes First U.S. Woman to Win Back-to-Back Discus Golds

Allman clinched gold before her final throw, but that did not stop her from posting a 69.50-meter throw to finish the competition.

ResultsNext slide: Amit Elor Cruises to Finals, Secures Wrestling's First Medal

Miles Partain and Andy Benesh Win in Straight Sets To Move On To the Quarterfinals

The duo defeated Italy 21-17 in set 1 and 21-18 in set 2 to keep their medal hopes alive

ResultsNext slide: Mixed Triathlon take silver in a photo finish
